   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>The "check" target in this Makefile controls recovery testing: 
<a href="https://github.com/openhatch/oh-restore/blob/master/Makefile">https://github.com/openhatch/oh-restore/blob/master/Makefile</a>

Does that pass muster? If so, please mark as resolved. Thanks!</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg2920">msg2920 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: paulproteus</th>
   <th>Date: 2012-01-28.01:48:46</th>
   <th>
    
   </th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>What it would take for you to be satisfied with this?

One thing we could do is, periodically:

* Prepare a disk image based on the most recent backup
* Boot that with user-mode-linux, KVM, qemu, or something similar
* Ensure that, within 10 minutes of the boot starting, if you make a request to
that VM for the URL <a href="http://openhatch.org/+yo_is_django_alive">http://openhatch.org/+yo_is_django_alive</a> , it returns the
string "success" just like on the real site.

Doing this would come at some non-trivial bandwidth cost, so I'm thinking it
makes sense to do it weekly or monthly.

Thoughts?</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
